Description:
Family Flexibility with Parkland Proximity
Moments from the open spaces of Taylors Creek Linear Park, this pristine single-level home occupies a wonderfully wide allotment providing a family lifestyle of immediate quality and versatility along with terrific scope to modernise and personalise. Immaculate from start to finish, the home's free-flowing interior comprises four generous bedrooms (all with built-in robes) and study/home office, master ensuite and main family bathroom complete with spa bath. Multiple living zones include an elegant formal lounge and adjoining dining area (both with chandeliers), spacious living room and light-filled family/meals area accompanied by a timber-cabinet kitchen with ample cupboard space. Other highlights include ducted heating and evaporative cooling, ducted vacuum, family-sized laundry, plus a wide backyard with established trees and handy storage shed, deep double garage (r/c) and horseshoe driveway with dual crossovers. Endless walking/cycling trails virtually at your doorstep, it also offers close proximity to popular schools including Overnewton College, public transport, local shopping precincts and easy freeway access.

Description:
Single Level Style, Sophistication and Space
Surrounded by picturesque parklands in a peaceful and prominent estate, this brilliantly renovated home manages to combine traditional space with modern tones and contemporary finishes.
Manicured lawns and landscaped gardens welcome you into the property, which begins with a beautifully bright and expansive formal living area which, like the warming pine floorboards and split-system air-conditioning, flow through to a stunning open plan family, meals and kitchen precinct.
Forming the centre-piece of this conducive layout, the sparkling modern kitchen features high-end stainless steel appliances including a built-in gas cook top, range hood, under bench oven and dishwasher as well as an abundance of quality bench and storage room.
A sprawling family room with study/home office nook provides yet another place to relax with friends and to get that last minute email sent, connecting cleverly to a fantastic outdoor entertainment zone.
Spacious bedrooms provide ample accommodation, all include built-in robes, the master has its own contemporary en-suite and a magnificent guest room enjoys direct access to the rear yard.
The incredible main bathroom is spectacular from beginning to end, featuring a walk-in double shower, modern tiling, heated towel rack and a feature free-standing bath.
An elevated covered seating space overlooks a private backyard with established gardens and plenty of grass for the kids and pets to explore.
Built for style and simplicity across one flawless level, ducted heating, additional air-conditioning, a separate laundry, double carport and a sun-drenched north facing aspect combine to complete an impressive package.
With Patterson Gardens almost at your doorstep, Lagoon Reserve and local preschools within walking distance, close proximity to Keilor Primary School and Keilor Plains Train Station, plus easy access to the Calder Freeway, Western Ring Road, the Melbourne CBD and Tullamarine Airport, flawless family living awaits.

Description:
Family Expanse in the Heart of Keilor Village
On approx 860sqm of land, moments from Lagoon Reserve in one of Keilor's premier streetscapes, this two-storey family residence provides an outstanding village lifestyle opportunity with its vast proportions, immediate quality and floorplan flexibility. Spacious and light-filled interior showcases four large bedrooms (master with balcony and walk-through robes to private ensuite), open study area, main family bathroom and two separate WCs (one on each level). Versatile living zones include a spacious lounge complete with wet-bar and wine cellar, expansive living area with open fireplace and cathedral ceilings leading through to the open dining area and adjoining kitchen with solid timber cabinetry and dishwasher. Other stand-out features include in-floor heating and reverse-cycle split-system air conditioning, alarm and CCTV, large laundry and excellent storage options throughout, plus an enormous backyard garden with in-ground pool and double garage via gated driveway. Walking distance to the Maribyrnong River along with village shops and eateries, it's also close to local buses, schools and sports facilities, as well as easy access the Calder Freeway.

Description:
Incomparable Serenity On 16.8 Acres (Approx.)
Boasting a prime position in a truly unique pocket of Keilor, this spectacular and rare land opportunity of approximately 16.8 acres is situated within metropolitan Melbourne while offering all the peace and quiet of a rural idyll. Placed with a rich history in the blue-ribbon market garden district, the fully irrigated fertile allotment provides a near-level parcel with good vehicular access. Delivering on versatility and size, the property enjoys a luscious setting ensconced by the natural beauty of the nearby Maribyrnong river and surrounds. As quality neighbouring homes attest, this is the perfect foundation for you to create your dream manor (STCA), or simply land bank and let time work its magic on your investment. The property also presents the ultimate in convenience with nearby Calder Freeway access and proximity to Melbourne international airport. Sought-after private and public schools are also close at hand, as well as trendy Keilor Village shops/cafes and major shopping centres including Watergardens, Highpoint and Westfield.

Description:
When Presentation & Location Matter!
This immaculate family home, tightly held by current owners for decades, offers well-located, low maintenance living in a blue-ribbon location and with quick easy access to local amenities, including walking distance to the Keilor Village local shops and cafes.
A classic brick and tile, circa early 1980's; the home exudes great charm and warmth, and is complete with elegant entry porch and foyer, three bedrooms, study/4th bedroom, two bathrooms, formal lounge/dining, casual living/meals, stylish updated kitchen, separate laundry, triple covered carparking plus extra room onsite, and a private covered deck for alfresco entertaining.
Meticulously cared for by its long-term owners, presentation shines and features include: quality window furnishings, stone benches in kitchen, stainless steel appliances, gas cooktop, ducted heating, evaporative cooling, timber-look vinyl flooring in casual living/kitchen/study, separate bath and shower in main bathroom, exposed aggregate driveway, and easy-care landscaped gardens.
A timeless design, there is a welcoming, cosy ambience throughout, almost a sense of familiarity; it's a lovely place to hang your hat and stay for a while...you'll see why existing owners have anchored down here for so long; it is simply delightful, and so very liveable.
Your entertaining needs can be catered for inside or out on the pergola; from formal dinners through to casual weekend BBQ's, you can accommodate your guests in impeccable style and comfort.
The deck would make the perfect spot for Christmas lunch...and your 'go to' place for your morning coffee or twilight sun-downers at 'wine o'clock'.
Inside and out, there is no immediate money to be spent; the living is easy, and the location is sought-after - with premium schools to choose from, wonderful parks in the local vicinity, and 18 kilometres to the CBD, you can embrace the quiet life without sacrificing convenience.
Start packing.

Description:
Fuss Free Entertainer
Brilliantly located within a stones throw from popular Keilor Village cafes and shops, this spacious two bedroom villa unit is sure to impress. Bright and fresh, open plan living area combines a spacious lounge, adjoining meals and sleek kitchen, showcasing two tone cabinetry and stainless appliances. Spanning out via glass stacking doors to an expansive peaked roof decking, providing the ideal entertaining zone or place to sit and relax at the end of the day. Two generous bedrooms have built in robes, serviced by a central bathroom displaying a glass top double vanity and oversize shower. Off street parking, via dual road access includes an enclosed carport plus remote garage. Further enhancements include polished floor boards, split system and ceiling fans. Convenient access to major arterials and bus routes makes commuting a breeze.Quality location, low maintenance and no body corporate involvement presents the ideal opportunity for those wishing to downsize or add to their investment portfolio.

Description:
A Real Surprise Package
In the heart of the 'Village' combining street frontage, this spectacular two bedroom one bathroom unit exudes modern flair and sophistication throughout. The spacious, light and airy kitchen is stunning with centred island, six burner 900mm gas cooktop, electric oven, dishwasher and soft close cabinetry, and flows seamlessly to the dining and living areas, all of which lay beneath high vaulted ceilings, and are surrounded by windows looking out onto the gardens beyond. The bedrooms boast new carpets and built in robes, whilst the huge bathroom showcases a deep bath, floating vanity, shower with rain head and cleverly concealed laundry. There's a private alfresco courtyard with low maintenance surrounds and room for outdoor dining and barbeque. Freshly painted, secure garage, additional car/caravan space at rear, evaporative cooling and ducted heating. Moments to Keilor Village, shopping, parklands, schools, public transport, easy access to freeway, airports and only 21kms to CBD. Inspection will surprise.

Description:
Quiet and Convenient with Impressive Family Credentials
A must-see for families that love to entertain, this single-level home is sure to make an impression with its generous proportions, quality features throughout and idyllic location in a secluded Keilor cul-de-sac. Beyond the attractive rendered facade discover a light-filled interior comprising four generous bedrooms (large master with luxurious ensuite), main family bathroom and separate WC. Dual living zones include a spacious lounge and dining area leading through to the family/meals area and timber-cabinet kitchen complete with Bosch oven and dishwasher. Other highlights include zoned ducted heating/refrigerated cooling, alarm and CCTV, new carpets throughout, solar power, modern laundry with stone benchtop and ample storage space. Step outside to an expansive undercover entertaining area with built-in BBQ plus a wide backyard with synthetic turf and handy storage shed, irrigated gardens all-round and front double carport. Close to the area's popular schools (including Overnewton College and St Augustine's Primary School), Keilor Village shops and eateries as well as public transport and easy access to the Calder Freeway. Simply move in and start living!

Description:
Valley Views Will Inspire
Boasting scenic valley views and lush garden block, approximately 534m2, adjoining a nature reserve, this immediately comfortable three bedroom brick home offers excellent renovation or rebuild potential (STCA). Tightly held for over twenty years, the neat and tidy property also provides an opportunity for first time buyers to move into a well-connected street popular with families. Immaculately presented, a traditional layout comprises welcoming entry flowing through to light filled, open plan lounge/dining zones where sliding glass doors open onto a large all-weather deck, perfect for alfresco dining and entertaining. Off to the side is a charming kitchen with gas/electric appliances, dishwasher, pantry and breakfast bar. Two out of three bedrooms have built-in-robes. They share a central bathroom, separate toilet and laundry. Complemented by landscaped surrounds, ducted heating/refrigerated cooling, ceiling fans, garden sheds, under house storage areas and off street driveway parking. Enjoys easy access to Overnewton College, St Augustines primary, Taylors Creek Linear Park, Keilor Village, shopping centres, buses and freeways.
